- where A is a substituted or unsubstituted C4 -C10 n-alkyl methacrylate, B is a substituted or unsubstituted C4 -C10 n-alkyl acrylate, C is selected from the group consisting of methyl methacrylate and ethyl methacrylate, and D is selected from the group consisting of methacrylic acid and acrylic acid; and


- where w, x, y, and z are weight percentages of comonomers in the polymeric binder, w is 5 to 40%, x is 5 to 40%, y is 10 to 70%, and z is 10 to 30%;


(b) at least one ethylenically unsaturated monomer; and


(c) at least one component selected from the group consisting of a photoinitiator and a photoinitiator system;

-  where A is a substituted or unsubstituted C4 -C10 n-alkyl methacrylate, B is a substituted or unsubstituted C4 -C10 n-alkyl acrylate, C is selected from the group consisting of methyl methacrylate and ethyl methacrylate, and D is selected from the group consisting of methacrylic acid and acrylic acid; and


-  where w, x, y, and z are weight percentages of comonomers in the polymeric binder, w is 5 to 40%, x is 5 to 40%, y is 10 to 70%, and z is 10 to 30%;


- (b) at least one ethylenically unsaturated monomer; and


- (c) at least one component selected from the group consisting of a photoinitiator and a photoinitiator system;

with the proviso that the photopolymerizable composition does not contain a basic compound used for the neutralization or partial neutralization of component (a);


(2) applying the photopolymerizable element to a copper clad substrate such that the photopolymerizable composition is in contact with the copper;


(3) imagewise exposing the photopolymerizable element to actinic radiation to afford an imagewise exposed photopolymerized element; and


(4) developing the imagewise exposed photopolymerized element of step (2) to form a resist image on the copper clad substrate having good sidewall geometry.
